Even without coding skills, you can get bugs fixed quickly by acting like a precise reporter rather than a programmer. The trick is to give the AI **observable facts** instead of guesses.

Here is the fewest-token formula that works:

---

### The Minimal Bug Template

Copy and paste this, then fill in the blanks:

```markdown
GOAL: I want to [what you are trying to do].

BUG: Instead, [what actually happens].

REPRODUCE: 
1. I open [file/app].
2. I click/type [exact action].
3. Then [next step].

ERROR: [paste the full error message, or write "no message, just crashes/freezes"].

CONTEXT: [what changed right before it broke? e.g., "I updated today" or "I added a photo"].
```

---

### Examples: Wasteful vs. Efficient

**Wasteful (too many tokens, too vague):**
> "Hey, so I'm not a programmer and this is really frustrating because I was using the app yesterday and everything was fine but now today when I try to do the thing it just doesn't work anymore and I don't know why, can you please help me fix it because I have a deadline..."

**Efficient (few tokens, high signal):**
> "BUG: App crashes when I upload a PNG over 5 MB.  
> ERROR: 'RuntimeException: Image too large'  
> REPRODUCE: Open app → Upload image → Select 6 MB PNG → Crash.  
> CONTEXT: Worked yesterday with JPGs."

---

### Zero-Coding Tips to Save Tokens

1. **Paste, don't paraphrase.**  
   If you see an error message, copy-paste the *exact* text. Don't say "something about memory." The AI needs the precise words.

2. **Screenshots are fine, but describe them in text.**  
   If you can't copy the error, type what you see:  
   `Red box at top says: "SyntaxError: Unexpected token"`  
   (The AI cannot see images in most chat interfaces.)

3. **Give one broken example, not your life story.**  
   Bad: "I tried a bunch of things..."  
   Good: "When I enter `hello` in the Name box, the Save button greys out."

4. **Say "worked before" if true.**  
   The most useful two words in debugging: `REGRESSION: It worked on Monday.` That immediately tells the AI to look at recent changes.

5. **If you have code, share the *smallest* piece that breaks.**  
   Don't dump 500 lines. Share just the 5–10 lines around the error. Even as a non-coder, you can usually spot the section the error message points to.

---

### The Absolute Shortest Version (Emergency Mode)

If you are truly token-starved, use this one-liner:

> **Error:** `[paste exact error]`  
> **Trigger:** `[the last thing you clicked/typed]`  
> **Wanted:** `[what you expected instead]`

That alone is often enough for the AI to solve 80% of common bugs.

---

**Bottom line:** The AI doesn't need you to know *why* it's broken; it needs you to describe *what* is broken with concrete steps. Facts cost fewer tokens than explanations.

